All of the accessories are in Unused condition. The paperwork includes an advertising pamphlet on this pistol and its accessories, a letter from the U.S. Historical Society confirming shipment, an invitation to purchase the pistol, a Certificate of Authenticity indicating this pistol is No. 1481 of 2500, a pamphlet on firing instructions, and an acknowledgement of receipt of deposit.
